              <p class="plan-price">₹249<span>/mo</span></p>
              <p class="plan-desc">100 websites, daily backups, more power</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p><strong>Important:</strong> These are introductory prices. Renewal rates are higher, so always buy for the longest term you can to lock in the low rate.</p>

          <h2>Speed & Performance</h2>
          <p>Hostinger uses LiteSpeed servers with built-in caching, which puts them ahead of many competitors at this price point. In our tests, pages loaded in under 1 second on average — impressive for shared hosting.</p>
          <p>They also offer a free CDN and their data centers are spread across the globe, so your visitors get fast load times regardless of location.</p>

          <h2>Ease of Use</h2>
          <p>Hostinger uses their own custom control panel called hPanel instead of the traditional cPanel. It's cleaner, simpler, and honestly easier for beginners. Installing WordPress or any other CMS takes literally one click.</p>

          <h2>Support</h2>
          <p>Hostinger offers 24/7 live chat support. In our experience, response times are fast — usually under 2 minutes. The only downside is there's no phone support, which some users prefer.</p>

          <h2>Is Hostinger worth it?</h2>
          <p>For beginners, small businesses, and anyone who wants reliable hosting without spending a lot — yes, absolutely. The combination of low pricing, solid performance, and ease of use makes it one of the best value options on the market today.</p>
          <p>If you need advanced features or WooCommerce-heavy sites, you might eventually outgrow shared hosting — but Hostinger's VPS plans are also competitively priced when that time comes.</p>

